{
  "stem": "18778.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after [INAUDIBLE] closed its doors because of attrition, we were solely [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My children were confirmed there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My son was bar mitzvahed there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I'm still there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I was active with the Women's Movement for Conservative Judaism, Philadelphia branch.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I went back to work when my children were about 11 and 13, and, again, went back into the art field.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I went to school, to night school again, and worked first, for-- I was art director for a manufacturing concern for 10 years.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I worked as a artist, graphic artist, and German correspondent for an electronic firm.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And then my last job was another 10-year stint with a printing house as graphic designer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My husband passed away, unfortunately, over nine years ago.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were just two weeks short of our 40th anniversary.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He had a bad heart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He had two open-heart surgeries, and he didn't make it out of the second one, unfortunately.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was my sadness that-- he was already retired at that time-- that, being 10 years younger, I wasn't entitled to be retired yet, and we couldn't play together.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And that's something that I've always regretted very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He busied himself with part-time work in real estate, and after he passed away, that was a very difficult adjustment for me-- I think, more than any other that I've had to make in my life, including the emigration and resettling in various countries.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But you do-- you learn to cope.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "I mean, you know, you cope with everything else, and you learn to cope with that too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My children were extremely supportive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "My daughter, at the time, lived in Montana.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So that wasn't so close, but my son was close by and a tremendous support for me.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
